rce";s:71:"https://customoverheaddoors.net/blog/reasons-your-garage-door-wont-work";s:6:"domain";s:23:"customoverheaddoors.net";}}s:9:"sentences";a:71:{i:0;s:72:"The most common cause of garage door issues is probably damaged rollers.";i:1;s:88:"These should be checked along with the hinges and other hardware for binding and damage.";i:2;s:132:"If you notice the rollers squealing or squeaking as you close or open the garage door they are likely the reason for a jerking door.";i:3;s:62:"Heres how to easily fix a garage door that jerks when opening.";i:4;s:92:"This issue tends to be worse when the door has been closed for a whileProducts used in this.";i:5;s:156:"Does your garage door jerk when it is opened after sitting closed for a whileChances are the vinyl weather stripping has gotten sticky or tacky and just ne.";i:6;s:148:"What happens is that the garage door travels too far down and loads up with downward pressure thus causing a big jerk when the pressure is released.";i:7;s:49:"Apparently this is pretty common and easy to fix.";i:8;s:114:"You should have two adjustments on your garage door opener that adjust the upward and downward travel of the door.";i:9;s:49:"Watch the opener carefully as it closes the door.";i:10;s:103:"You will see it bend a little as it stores the energy it took to force the door on to the garage floor.";i:11;s:76:"When you open the door some of that energy returns in the form of a rebound.";i:12;s:25:"That is the jerk you see.";i:13;s:22:"Here is an Experiment.";i:14;s:49:"Watch the opener carefully as it closes the door.";i:15;s:103:"You will see it bend a little as it stores the energy it took to force the door on to the garage floor.";i:16;s:76:"When you open the door some of that energy returns in the form of a rebound.";i:17;s:25:"That is the jerk you see.";i:18;s:22:"Here is an Experiment.";i:19;s:29:"Garage door jerks on opening.";i:20;s:99:"I have tried limit and force adjustments and checked door movement in tracks not sticking to floor.";i:21;s:73:"I had a chain come off the sprocket on my chamberlain garage door opener.";i:22;s:23:"I loosened the nuts to.";i:23;s:77:"There are several reasons why your garage door jerks when closing or opening.";i:24;s:83:"Common causes are a bent track bad rollers or problems with the garage door opener.";i:25;s:129:"You cant afford to ignore these issues as they will strain your opener and if ignored can burn out the motor on your garage door.";i:26;s:34:"Check the garage door for binding.";i:27;s:32:"Check the closing Force control.";i:28;s:54:"Door starts up but STOPS before it is completely open.";i:29;s:59:"Check if limits are properly set and adjust them as needed.";i:30;s:104:"Be sure the garage door opener and springs are in good repair properly lubricated adjusted and balanced.";i:31;s:40:"Check the openingclosing Force controls.";i:32;s:140:"If you notice the rollers screeching or squeaking as you close or open the garage door they are likely the justification for a jerking door.";i:33;s:139:"The garage door engine is a straightforward electric engine appended to some type of chain belt or pole that interfaces it to the entryway.";i:34;s:76:"Fixing an electric engine is past the extent of this instructional exercise.";i:35;s:43:"Garage door jerks when opening and closing.";i:36;s:74:"Last weekend my Garage door wouldnt open at all just made a humming sound.";i:37;s:121:"My husband played around with the opener Crafstman 12 HP 13953975SRT model and adjusted something and it started working.";i:38;s:104:"Disconnect the door from the opener and manually roll it up and down and check for spots where it binds.";i:39;s:69:"If the door itself doesnt bind then start looking at the opener unit.";i:40;s:104:"Once your overhead door rollers hit some debris on the tracks it will result in the jerking of the door.";i:41;s:87:"Other possible problems can be from the cables or the motor in your garage door opener.";i:42;s:102:"In case your garage door jerks 